
[1]greencloth

   GREE'NCLOTH, n. A board or court of justice held in the counting house
   of the British king's household, composed of the lord steward and the
   officers under him. This court has the charge and cognizance of all
   matters of justice in the king's household, with power to correct
   offenders and keep the peace of the verge, or jurisdiction of the
   court-royal, which extends every way two hundred yards from the gate of
   the palace.
